var book = {
	"name": "Nehemiah",
	"numChapters": 13,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>The words of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12298A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12298A\"></sup>Nehemiah the son of Hacaliah.Now it happened in the month of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12298B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12298B\"></sup>Chislev, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12298C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12298C\"></sup>in the twentieth year, as I was in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12298D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12298D\"></sup>Susa the citadel,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12299E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12299E\"></sup>Hanani, one of my brothers, came with certain men from Judah. And I asked them concerning the Jews who escaped, who had survived the exile, and concerning Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And they said to me, “The remnant there in the province who had survived the exile is in great trouble and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12300F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12300F\"></sup>shame. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12300G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12300G\"></sup>The wall of Jerusalem is broken down, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12300H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12300H\"></sup>and its gates are destroyed by fire.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>As soon as I heard these words I <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12301I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12301I\"></sup>sat down and wept and mourned for days, and I continued fasting and praying before the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12301J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12301J\"></sup>God of heaven.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And I said, “O <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> God of heaven, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12302K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12302K\"></sup>the great and awesome God who keeps covenant and steadfast love with those who love him and keep his commandments,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12303L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12303L\"></sup>let your ear be attentive and your eyes open, to hear the prayer of your servant that I now pray before you day and night for the people of Israel your servants, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12303M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12303M\"></sup>confessing the sins of the people of Israel, which we have sinned against you. Even <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12303N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12303N\"></sup>I and my father's house have sinned.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12304O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12304O\"></sup>We have acted very corruptly against you and have not kept the commandments, the statutes, and the rules <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12304P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12304P\"></sup>that you commanded your servant Moses.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Remember the word that you commanded your servant Moses, saying, ‘If you are unfaithful, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12305Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12305Q\"></sup>I will scatter you among the peoples,",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12306R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12306R\"></sup>but if you return to me and keep my commandments and do them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12306S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12306S\"></sup>though your outcasts are in the uttermost parts of heaven, from there I will gather them and bring them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12306T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12306T\"></sup>to the place that I have chosen, to make my name dwell there.’",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12307U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12307U\"></sup>They are your servants and your people, whom you have redeemed by your great power and by your strong hand.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>O Lord, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12308V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12308V\"></sup>let your ear be attentive to the prayer of your servant, and to the prayer of your servants who delight to fear your name, and give success to your servant today, and grant him mercy in the sight of this man.”Now I was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12308W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12308W\"></sup>cupbearer to the king."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>In the month of Nisan, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12309A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12309A\"></sup>in the twentieth year of King <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12309B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12309B\"></sup>Artaxerxes, when wine was before him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12309C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12309C\"></sup>I took up the wine and gave it to the king. Now I had not been sad in his presence.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the king said to me, “Why is your face sad, seeing you are not sick? This is nothing but <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12310D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12310D\"></sup>sadness of the heart.” Then I was very much afraid.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>I said to the king, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12311E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12311E\"></sup>“Let the king live forever! Why should not my face be sad, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12311F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12311F\"></sup>when the city, the place of my fathers' graves, lies in ruins, and its gates have been destroyed by fire?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the king said to me, “What are you requesting?” So I prayed <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12312G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12312G\"></sup>to the God of heaven.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And I said to the king, “If it pleases the king, and if your servant has found favor in your sight, that you send me to Judah, to the city of my fathers' graves, that I may rebuild it.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And the king said to me (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12314H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12314H\"></sup>the queen sitting beside him), “How long will you be gone, and when will you return?” So it pleased the king to send me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12314I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12314I\"></sup>when I had given him a time.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And I said to the king, “If it pleases the king, let letters be given me <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12315J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12315J\"></sup>to the governors of the province Beyond the River, that they may let me pass through until I come to Judah,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and a letter to Asaph, the keeper of the king's forest, that he may give me timber to make beams for the gates of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12316K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12316K\"></sup>the fortress of the temple, and for the wall of the city, and for the house that I shall occupy.” And the king granted me what I asked, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12316L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12316L\"></sup>for the good hand of my God was upon me.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then I came to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12317M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12317M\"></sup>the governors of the province Beyond the River and gave them the king's letters. Now the king had sent with me officers of the army and horsemen.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>But when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12318N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12318N\"></sup>Sanballat the Horonite and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12318O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12318O\"></sup>Tobiah the Ammonite servant heard this, it displeased them greatly that someone had come to seek the welfare of the people of Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12319P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12319P\"></sup>So I went to Jerusalem and was there three days.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then I arose in the night, I and a few men with me. And I told no one what my God had put into my heart to do for Jerusalem. There was no animal with me but the one on which I rode.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>I went out by night by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12321Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12321Q\"></sup>the Valley Gate to the Dragon Spring and to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12321R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12321R\"></sup>the Dung Gate, and I inspected the walls of Jerusalem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12321S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12321S\"></sup>that were broken down <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12321T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12321T\"></sup>and its gates that had been destroyed by fire.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Then I went on to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12322U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12322U\"></sup>the Fountain Gate and to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12322V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12322V\"></sup>the King's Pool, but there was no room for the animal that was under me to pass.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Then I went up in the night <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12323W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12323W\"></sup>by the valley and inspected the wall, and I turned back and entered by the Valley Gate, and so returned.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And the officials did not know where I had gone or what I was doing, and I had not yet told the Jews, the priests, the nobles, the officials, and the rest who were to do the work.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Then I said to them, “You see the trouble we are in, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12325X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12325X\"></sup>how Jerusalem lies in ruins with its gates burned. Come, let us build the wall of Jerusalem, that we may no longer <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12325Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12325Y\"></sup>suffer derision.”",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And I told them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12326Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12326Z\"></sup>of the hand of my God that had been upon me for good, and also of the words that the king had spoken to me. And they said, “Let us rise up and build.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12326AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12326AA\"></sup>So they strengthened their hands for the good work.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>But when Sanballat the Horonite and Tobiah the Ammonite servant and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12327AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12327AB\"></sup>Geshem the Arab heard of it, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12327AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12327AC\"></sup>they jeered at us and despised us and said, “What is this thing that you are doing? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12327AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12327AD\"></sup>Are you rebelling against the king?”",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then I replied to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12328AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12328AE\"></sup>“The God of heaven will make us prosper, and we his servants will arise and build, but you have no portion or right or claim in Jerusalem.”"
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>Then <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12329A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12329A\"></sup>Eliashib the high priest rose up with his brothers the priests, and they built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12329B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12329B\"></sup>the Sheep Gate. They consecrated it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12329C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12329C\"></sup>set its doors. They consecrated it as far as the Tower of the Hundred, as far as the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12329D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12329D\"></sup>Tower of Hananel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And next to him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12330E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12330E\"></sup>the men of Jericho built. And next to them Zaccur the son of Imri built.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>The sons of Hassenaah built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12331F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12331F\"></sup>the Fish Gate. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12331G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12331G\"></sup>They laid its beams and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12331H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12331H\"></sup>set its doors, its bolts, and its bars.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And next to them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12332I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12332I\"></sup>Meremoth the son of Uriah, son of Hakkoz repaired. And next to them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12332J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12332J\"></sup>Meshullam the son of Berechiah, son of Meshezabel repaired. And next to them Zadok the son of Baana repaired.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And next to them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12333K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12333K\"></sup>the Tekoites repaired, but their nobles would not stoop to serve their Lord.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Joiada the son of Paseah and Meshullam the son of Besodeiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12334L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12334L\"></sup>repaired the Gate of Yeshanah. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12334M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12334M\"></sup>They laid its beams and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12334N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12334N\"></sup>set its doors, its bolts, and its bars.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And next to them repaired Melatiah the Gibeonite and Jadon the Meronothite, the men of Gibeon and of Mizpah, the seat of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12335O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12335O\"></sup>the governor of the province Beyond the River.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Next to them Uzziel the son of Harhaiah, goldsmiths, repaired. Next to him Hananiah, one of the perfumers, repaired, and they restored Jerusalem as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12336P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12336P\"></sup>the Broad Wall.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Next to them Rephaiah the son of Hur, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12337Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12337Q\"></sup>ruler of half the district of Jerusalem, repaired.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Next to them Jedaiah the son of Harumaph repaired opposite his house. And next to him Hattush the son of Hashabneiah repaired.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Malchijah the son of Harim and Hasshub the son of Pahath-moab repaired another section and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12339R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12339R\"></sup>the Tower of the Ovens.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Next to him Shallum the son of Hallohesh, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12340S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12340S\"></sup>ruler of half the district of Jerusalem, repaired, he and his daughters.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Hanun and the inhabitants of Zanoah repaired <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12341T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12341T\"></sup>the Valley Gate. They rebuilt it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12341U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12341U\"></sup>set its doors, its bolts, and its bars, and repaired a thousand cubits of the wall, as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12341V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12341V\"></sup>the Dung Gate.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Malchijah the son of Rechab, ruler of the district of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12342W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12342W\"></sup>Beth-haccherem, repaired <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12342X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12342X\"></sup>the Dung Gate. He rebuilt it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12342Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12342Y\"></sup>set its doors, its bolts, and its bars.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And Shallum the son of Col-hozeh, ruler of the district of Mizpah, repaired <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12343Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12343Z\"></sup>the Fountain Gate. He rebuilt it and covered it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12343AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12343AA\"></sup>set its doors, its bolts, and its bars. And he built the wall of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12343AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12343AB\"></sup>the Pool of Shelah of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12343AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12343AC\"></sup>the king's garden, as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12343AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12343AD\"></sup>the stairs that go down from the city of David.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>After him Nehemiah the son of Azbuk, ruler of half the district of Beth-zur, repaired to a point opposite <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12344AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12344AE\"></sup>the tombs of David, as far as <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12344AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12344AF\"></sup>the artificial pool, and as far as the house of the mighty men.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>After him the Levites repaired: Rehum the son of Bani. Next to him Hashabiah, ruler of half the district of Keilah, repaired for his district.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>After him their brothers repaired: Bavvai the son of Henadad, ruler of half the district of Keilah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Next to him Ezer the son of Jeshua, ruler of Mizpah, repaired another section opposite the ascent to the armory at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12347AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12347AG\"></sup>the buttress.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>After him Baruch the son of Zabbai repaired another section from the buttress to the door of the house of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12348AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12348AH\"></sup>Eliashib the high priest.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>After him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12349AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12349AI\"></sup>Meremoth the son of Uriah, son of Hakkoz repaired another section from the door of the house of Eliashib to the end of the house of Eliashib.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>After him the priests, the men of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12350AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12350AJ\"></sup>the surrounding area, repaired.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>After them Benjamin and Hasshub repaired opposite their house. After them Azariah the son of Maaseiah, son of Ananiah repaired beside his own house.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>After him Binnui the son of Henadad repaired another section, from the house of Azariah to the buttress and to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12352AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12352AK\"></sup>the corner.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Palal the son of Uzai repaired opposite the buttress and the tower projecting from the upper house of the king at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12353AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12353AL\"></sup>the court of the guard. After him Pedaiah the son of Parosh",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12354AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12354AM\"></sup>and the temple servants living on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12354AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12354AN\"></sup>Ophel repaired to a point opposite <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12354AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12354AO\"></sup>the Water Gate on the east and the projecting tower.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>After him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12355AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12355AP\"></sup>the Tekoites repaired another section opposite the great projecting tower as far as the wall of Ophel.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>Above <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12356AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12356AQ\"></sup>the Horse Gate the priests repaired, each one opposite his own house.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>After them Zadok the son of Immer repaired opposite his own house. After him Shemaiah the son of Shecaniah, the keeper of the East Gate, repaired.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>After him Hananiah the son of Shelemiah and Hanun the sixth son of Zalaph repaired another section. After him <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12358AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12358AR\"></sup>Meshullam the son of Berechiah repaired opposite <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12358AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12358AS\"></sup>his chamber.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>After him Malchijah, one of the goldsmiths, repaired as far as the house of the temple servants and of the merchants, opposite the Muster Gate, and to the upper chamber of the corner.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And between the upper chamber of the corner and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12360AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12360AT\"></sup>the Sheep Gate the goldsmiths and the merchants repaired."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span> Now when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12361A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12361A\"></sup>Sanballat heard that we were building the wall, he was angry and greatly enraged, and he jeered at the Jews.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And he said in the presence of his brothers and of the army of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12362B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12362B\"></sup>Samaria, “What are these feeble Jews doing? Will they restore it for themselves? Will they sacrifice? Will they finish up in a day? Will they revive the stones out of the heaps of rubbish, and burned ones at that?”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12363C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12363C\"></sup>Tobiah the Ammonite was beside him, and he said, “Yes, what they are building—<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12363D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12363D\"></sup>if a fox goes up on it he will break down their stone wall!”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12364E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12364E\"></sup>Hear, O our God, for we are despised. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12364F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12364F\"></sup>Turn back their taunt on their own heads and give them up to be plundered in a land where they are captives.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12365G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12365G\"></sup>Do not cover their guilt, and let not their sin be blotted out from your sight, for they have provoked you to anger in the presence of the builders.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>So we built the wall. And all the wall was joined together to half its height, for the people had a mind to work.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup> But when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12367H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12367H\"></sup>Sanballat and Tobiah and the Arabs and the Ammonites and the Ashdodites heard that the repairing of the walls of Jerusalem was going forward and that the breaches were beginning to be closed, they were very angry.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12368I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12368I\"></sup>And they all plotted together to come and fight against Jerusalem and to cause confusion in it.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And we prayed to our God and set a guard as a protection against them day and night.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>In Judah it was said, “The strength of those who bear the burdens is failing. There is too much rubble. By ourselves we will not be able to rebuild the wall.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>And our enemies said, “They will not know or see till we come among them and kill them and stop the work.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>At that time the Jews who lived near them came from all directions and said to us ten times, “You must return to us.”",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>So in the lowest parts of the space behind the wall, in open places, I stationed the people by their clans, with their swords, their spears, and their bows.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And I looked and arose and said to the nobles and to the officials and to the rest of the people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12374J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12374J\"></sup>“Do not be afraid of them. Remember the Lord, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12374K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12374K\"></sup>who is great and awesome, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12374L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12374L\"></sup>and fight for your brothers, your sons, your daughters, your wives, and your homes.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>When our enemies heard that it was known to us <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12375M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12375M\"></sup>and that God had frustrated their plan, we all returned to the wall, each to his work.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>From that day on, half of my servants worked on construction, and half held the spears, shields, bows, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12376N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12376N\"></sup>coats of mail. And the leaders stood behind the whole house of Judah,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>who were building on the wall. Those who carried burdens were loaded in such a way that each labored on the work with one hand and held his weapon with the other.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And each of the builders had his sword strapped at his side while he built. The man who sounded the trumpet was beside me.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>And I said to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12379O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12379O\"></sup>the nobles and to the officials and to the rest of the people, “The work is great and widely spread, and we are separated on the wall, far from one another.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>In the place where you hear the sound of the trumpet, rally to us there. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12380P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12380P\"></sup>Our God will fight for us.”",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So we labored at the work, and half of them held the spears from the break of dawn until the stars came out.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>I also said to the people at that time, “Let every man and his servant pass the night within Jerusalem, that they may be a guard for us by night and may labor by day.”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So neither I nor my brothers nor my servants nor the men of the guard who followed me, none of us took off our clothes; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12383Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12383Q\"></sup>each kept his weapon at his right hand."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>Now there arose <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12384A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12384A\"></sup>a great outcry of the people and of their wives <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12384B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12384B\"></sup>against their Jewish brothers.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>For there were those who said, “With our sons and our daughters, we are many. So let us get grain, that we may eat and keep alive.”",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>There were also those who said, “We are mortgaging our fields, our vineyards, and our houses to get grain because of the famine.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And there were those who said, “We have borrowed money for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12387C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12387C\"></sup>the king's tax on our fields and our vineyards.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Now <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12388D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12388D\"></sup>our flesh is as the flesh of our brothers, our children are as their children. Yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12388E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12388E\"></sup>we are forcing our sons and our daughters to be slaves, and some of our daughters have already been enslaved, but it is not in our power to help it, for other men have our fields and our vineyards.”",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>I was very angry when I heard <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12389F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12389F\"></sup>their outcry and these words.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>I took counsel with myself, and I brought charges against the nobles and the officials. I said to them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12390G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12390G\"></sup>“You are exacting interest, each from his brother.” And I held a great assembly against them",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and said to them, “We, as far as we are able, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12391H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12391H\"></sup>have bought back our Jewish brothers who have been sold to the nations, but you even sell your brothers that they may be sold to us!” They were silent and could not find a word to say.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>So I said, “The thing that you are doing is not good. Ought you not to walk <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12392I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12392I\"></sup>in the fear of our God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12392J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12392J\"></sup>to prevent the taunts of the nations our enemies?",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Moreover, I and my brothers and my servants are lending them money and grain. Let us abandon this exacting of interest.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Return to them this very day their fields, their vineyards, their olive orchards, and their houses, and the percentage of money, grain, wine, and oil that you have been exacting from them.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then they said, “We will restore these and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12395K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12395K\"></sup>require nothing from them. We will do as you say.” And I called the priests and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12395L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12395L\"></sup>made them swear <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12395M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12395M\"></sup>to do as they had promised.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12396N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12396N\"></sup>I also shook out the fold of my garment and said, “So may God shake out every man from his house and from his labor who does not keep this promise. So may he be shaken out and emptied.” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12396O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12396O\"></sup>And all the assembly said “Amen” and praised the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>. And the people did as they had promised.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Moreover, from the time that I was appointed to be their governor in the land of Judah, from <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12397P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12397P\"></sup>the twentieth year to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12397Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12397Q\"></sup>the thirty-second year of Artaxerxes the king, twelve years, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12397R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12397R\"></sup>neither I nor my brothers ate the food allowance of the governor.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The former governors who were before me laid heavy burdens on the people and took from them for their daily ration forty shekels of silver. Even their servants lorded it over the people. But I did not do so, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12398S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12398S\"></sup>because of the fear of God.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>I also persevered in the work on this wall, and we acquired no land, and all my servants were gathered there for the work.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Moreover, there were <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12400T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12400T\"></sup>at my table 150 men, Jews and officials, besides those who came to us from the nations that were around us.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12401U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12401U\"></sup>Now what was prepared at my expense for each day was one ox and six choice sheep and birds, and every ten days all kinds of wine in abundance. Yet for all this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12401V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12401V\"></sup>I did not demand the food allowance of the governor, because the service was too heavy on this people.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12402W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12402W\"></sup>Remember for my good, O my God, all that I have done for this people."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>Now when <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12403A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12403A\"></sup>Sanballat and Tobiah and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12403B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12403B\"></sup>Geshem the Arab and the rest of our enemies heard that I had built the wall and that there was no breach left in it (<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12403C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12403C\"></sup>although up to that time I had not set up the doors in the gates),",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Sanballat and Geshem sent to me, saying, “Come and let us meet together at Hakkephirim in the plain of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12404D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12404D\"></sup>Ono.” But they intended to do me harm.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And I sent messengers to them, saying, “I am doing a great work and I cannot come down. Why should the work stop while I leave it and come down to you?”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And they sent to me four times in this way, and I answered them in the same manner.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>In the same way Sanballat for the fifth time sent his servant to me with an open letter in his hand.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>In it was written, “It is reported among the nations, and Geshem also says it, that you and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12408E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12408E\"></sup>the Jews intend to rebel; that is why you are building the wall. And according to these reports you wish to become their king.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And you have also set up prophets to proclaim concerning you in Jerusalem, ‘There is a king in Judah.’ And now the king will hear of these reports. So now come and let us take counsel together.”",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Then I sent to him, saying, “No such things as you say have been done, for you are inventing them out of your own mind.”",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>For they all wanted to frighten us, thinking, “Their hands will drop from the work, and it will not be done.” But now, O God, strengthen my hands.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Now when I went into the house of Shemaiah the son of Delaiah, son of Mehetabel, who was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12412F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12412F\"></sup>confined to his home, he said, “Let us meet together in the house of God, within the temple. Let us close the doors of the temple, for they are coming to kill you. They are coming to kill you by night.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>But I said, “Should such a man as I run away? And what man such as I could go into the temple and live? I will not go in.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And I understood and saw that God had not sent him, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12414G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12414G\"></sup>but he had pronounced the prophecy against me because Tobiah and Sanballat had hired him.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>For this purpose he was hired, that I should be afraid and act in this way and sin, and so they could give me a bad name in order to taunt me.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12416H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12416H\"></sup>Remember Tobiah and Sanballat, O my God, according to these things that they did, and also <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12416I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12416I\"></sup>the prophetess Noadiah and the rest of the prophets who wanted to make me afraid.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>So the wall was finished on the twenty-fifth day of the month Elul, in fifty-two days.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12418J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12418J\"></sup>when all our enemies heard of it, all the nations around us were afraid and fell greatly in their own esteem, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12418K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12418K\"></sup>for they perceived that this work had been accomplished with the help of our God.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Moreover, in those days the nobles of Judah sent many letters to Tobiah, and Tobiah's letters came to them.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>For many in Judah were bound by oath to him, because he was the son-in-law of Shecaniah the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12420L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12420L\"></sup>Arah: and his son Jehohanan had taken the daughter of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12420M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12420M\"></sup>Meshullam the son of Berechiah as his wife.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Also they spoke of his good deeds in my presence and reported my words to him. And Tobiah sent letters to make me afraid."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>Now when the wall had been built <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12422A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12422A\"></sup>and I had set up the doors, and the gatekeepers, the singers, and the Levites had been appointed,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>I gave <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12423B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12423B\"></sup>my brother Hanani and Hananiah the governor of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12423C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12423C\"></sup>the castle charge over Jerusalem, for he was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12423D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12423D\"></sup>a more faithful and God-fearing man than many.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>And I said to them, “Let not the gates of Jerusalem be opened until the sun is hot. And while they are still standing guard, let them shut and bar the doors. Appoint guards from among the inhabitants of Jerusalem, some at their guard posts and some in front of their own homes.”",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>The city was wide and large, but the people within it were few, and no houses had been rebuilt.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then my God put it into my heart to assemble the nobles and the officials and the people to be enrolled by genealogy. And I found the book of the genealogy of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12426E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12426E\"></sup>those who came up at the first, and I found written in it:",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12427F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12427F\"></sup>These were the people of the province who came up out of the captivity of those exiles whom Nebuchadnezzar the king of Babylon had carried into exile. They returned to Jerusalem and Judah, each to his town.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>They came with Zerubbabel, Jeshua, Nehemiah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12428G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12428G\"></sup>Azariah, Raamiah, Nahamani, Mordecai, Bilshan, Mispereth, Bigvai, Nehum, Baanah.The number of the men of the people of Israel:",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>the sons of Parosh, 2,172.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>The sons of Shephatiah, 372.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>The sons of Arah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12431H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12431H\"></sup>652.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>The sons of Pahath-moab, namely the sons of Jeshua and Joab, 2,818.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12433I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12433I\"></sup>Elam, 1,254.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>The sons of Zattu, 845.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The sons of Zaccai, 760.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12436J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12436J\"></sup>Binnui, 648.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>The sons of Bebai, 628.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The sons of Azgad, 2,322.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The sons of Adonikam, 667.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The sons of Bigvai, 2,067.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The sons of Adin, 655.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>The sons of Ater, namely of Hezekiah, 98.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The sons of Hashum, 328.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12444K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12444K\"></sup>Bezai, 324.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>The sons of Hariph, 112.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12446L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12446L\"></sup>Gibeon, 95.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>The men of Bethlehem and Netophah, 188.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>The men of Anathoth, 128.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>The men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12449M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12449M\"></sup>of Beth-azmaveth, 42.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>The men of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12450N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12450N\"></sup>Kiriath-jearim, Chephirah, and Beeroth, 743.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>The men of Ramah and Geba, 621.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The men of Michmas, 122.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>The men of Bethel and Ai, 123.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>The men of the other Nebo, 52.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12455O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12455O\"></sup>the other Elam, 1,254.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>The sons of Harim, 320.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The sons of Jericho, 345.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>The sons of Lod, Hadid, and Ono, 721.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>The sons of Senaah, 3,930.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>The priests: the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12460P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12460P\"></sup>Jedaiah, namely the house of Jeshua, 973.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12461Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12461Q\"></sup>Immer, 1,052.",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12462R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12462R\"></sup>Pashhur, 1,247.",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>The sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12463S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12463S\"></sup>Harim, 1,017.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>The Levites: the sons of Jeshua, namely of Kadmiel of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12464T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12464T\"></sup>Hodevah, 74.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>The singers: the sons of Asaph, 148.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>The gatekeepers: the sons of Shallum, the sons of Ater, the sons of Talmon, the sons of Akkub, the sons of Hatita, the sons of Shobai, 138.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>The temple servants: the sons of Ziha, the sons of Hasupha, the sons of Tabbaoth,",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>the sons of Keros, the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12468U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12468U\"></sup>Sia, the sons of Padon,",
			"48": "<sup class=\"versenum\">48 </sup>the sons of Lebana, the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12469V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12469V\"></sup>Hagaba, the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12469W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12469W\"></sup>Shalmai,",
			"49": "<sup class=\"versenum\">49 </sup>the sons of Hanan, the sons of Giddel, the sons of Gahar,",
			"50": "<sup class=\"versenum\">50 </sup>the sons of Reaiah, the sons of Rezin, the sons of Nekoda,",
			"51": "<sup class=\"versenum\">51 </sup>the sons of Gazzam, the sons of Uzza, the sons of Paseah,",
			"52": "<sup class=\"versenum\">52 </sup>the sons of Besai, the sons of Meunim, the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12473X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12473X\"></sup>Nephushesim,",
			"53": "<sup class=\"versenum\">53 </sup>the sons of Bakbuk, the sons of Hakupha, the sons of Harhur,",
			"54": "<sup class=\"versenum\">54 </sup>the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12475Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12475Y\"></sup>Bazlith, the sons of Mehida, the sons of Harsha,",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>the sons of Barkos, the sons of Sisera, the sons of Temah,",
			"56": "<sup class=\"versenum\">56 </sup>the sons of Neziah, the sons of Hatipha.",
			"57": "<sup class=\"versenum\">57 </sup>The sons of Solomon's servants: the sons of Sotai, the sons of Sophereth, the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12478Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12478Z\"></sup>Perida,",
			"58": "<sup class=\"versenum\">58 </sup>the sons of Jaala, the sons of Darkon, the sons of Giddel,",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>the sons of Shephatiah, the sons of Hattil, the sons of Pochereth-hazzebaim, the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12480AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12480AA\"></sup>Amon.",
			"60": "<sup class=\"versenum\">60 </sup>All the temple servants and the sons of Solomon's servants were 392.",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12482AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12482AB\"></sup>The following were those who came up from Tel-melah, Tel-harsha, Cherub, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12482AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12482AC\"></sup>Addon, and Immer, but they could not prove their fathers' houses nor their descent, whether they belonged to Israel:",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>the sons of Delaiah, the sons of Tobiah, the sons of Nekoda, 642.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>Also, of the priests: the sons of Hobaiah, the sons of Hakkoz, the sons of Barzillai (who had taken a wife of the daughters of Barzillai the Gileadite and was called by their name).",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>These sought their registration among those enrolled in the genealogies, but it was not found there, so they were excluded from the priesthood as unclean.",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12486AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12486AD\"></sup>The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12486AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12486AE\"></sup>governor told them that they were not to partake of the most holy food until a priest with Urim and Thummim should arise.",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>The whole assembly together was 42,360,",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>besides their male and female servants, of whom there were 7,337. And they had 245 singers, male and female.",
			"68": "<sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup>Their horses were 736, their mules 245,",
			"69": "<sup class=\"versenum\">69 </sup>their camels 435, and their donkeys 6,720.",
			"70": "<sup class=\"versenum\">70 </sup>Now some of the heads of fathers' houses gave to the work. The <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12491AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12491AF\"></sup>governor gave to the treasury 1,000 darics of gold, 50 basins, 30 priests' garments and 500 minas of silver.",
			"71": "<sup class=\"versenum\">71 </sup>And some of the heads of fathers' houses gave into the treasury of the work 20,000 darics of gold and 2,200 minas of silver.",
			"72": "<sup class=\"versenum\">72 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12493AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12493AG\"></sup>And what the rest of the people gave was 20,000 darics of gold, 2,000 minas of silver, and 67 priests' garments.",
			"73": "<sup class=\"versenum\">73 </sup>So the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers, the singers, some of the people, the temple servants, and all Israel, lived in their towns.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12494AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12494AH\"></sup>And when the seventh month had come, the people of Israel were in their towns."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>And all the people gathered as one man into the square before <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12495A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12495A\"></sup>the Water Gate. And they told <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12495B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12495B\"></sup>Ezra the scribe to bring the Book of the Law of Moses that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded Israel.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>So Ezra the priest <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12496C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12496C\"></sup>brought the Law before the assembly, both men and women and all who could understand what they heard, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12496D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12496D\"></sup>on the first day of the seventh month.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12497E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12497E\"></sup>And he read from it facing the square before the Water Gate from early morning until midday, in the presence of the men and the women and those who could understand. And the ears of all the people were attentive to the Book of the Law.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And Ezra the scribe stood on a wooden platform that they had made for the purpose. And beside him stood Mattithiah, Shema, Anaiah, Uriah, Hilkiah, and Maaseiah on his right hand, and Pedaiah, Mishael, Malchijah, Hashum, Hashbaddanah, Zechariah, and Meshullam on his left hand.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>And Ezra opened the book in the sight of all the people, for he was above all the people, and as he opened it all the people stood.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>And Ezra blessed the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the great God, and all the people answered, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12500F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12500F\"></sup>“Amen, Amen,” <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12500G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12500G\"></sup>lifting up their hands. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12500H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12500H\"></sup>And they bowed their heads and worshiped the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> with their faces to the ground.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12501I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12501I\"></sup>Also Jeshua, Bani, Sherebiah, Jamin, Akkub, Shabbethai, Hodiah, Maaseiah, Kelita, Azariah, Jozabad, Hanan, Pelaiah, the Levites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12501J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12501J\"></sup>helped the people to understand the Law, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12501K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12501K\"></sup>while the people remained in their places.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>They read from the book, from the Law of God, clearly, and they gave the sense, so that the people understood the reading.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Nehemiah, who was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12503L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12503L\"></sup>the governor, and Ezra <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12503M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12503M\"></sup>the priest and scribe, and the Levites who taught the people said to all the people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12503N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12503N\"></sup>“This day is holy to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12503O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12503O\"></sup>do not mourn or weep.” For all the people wept as they heard the words of the Law.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then he said to them, “Go your way. Eat the fat and drink sweet wine and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12504P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12504P\"></sup>send portions to anyone who has nothing ready, for this day is holy to our Lord. And do not be grieved, for the joy of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> is your strength.”",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>So the Levites calmed all the people, saying, “Be quiet, for this day is holy; do not be grieved.”",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>And all the people went their way to eat and drink and to send portions and to make great rejoicing, because <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12506Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12506Q\"></sup>they had understood the words that were declared to them.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>On the second day the heads of fathers' houses of all the people, with the priests and the Levites, came together to Ezra the scribe in order to study the words of the Law.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>And they found it written in the Law that the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had commanded by Moses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12508R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12508R\"></sup>that the people of Israel should dwell in booths during the feast of the seventh month,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and that they should proclaim it and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12509S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12509S\"></sup>publish it in all their towns and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12509T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12509T\"></sup>in Jerusalem, “Go out to the hills and bring <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12509U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12509U\"></sup>branches of olive, wild olive, myrtle, palm, and other leafy trees to make booths, as it is written.”",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So the people went out and brought them and made booths for themselves, each <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12510V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12510V\"></sup>on his roof, and in their courts and in the courts of the house of God, and in the square at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12510W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12510W\"></sup>the Water Gate and in the square at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12510X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12510X\"></sup>the Gate of Ephraim.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>And all the assembly of those who had returned from the captivity made booths and lived in the booths, for from the days of Jeshua the son of Nun to that day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12511Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12511Y\"></sup>the people of Israel had not done so. And there was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12511Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12511Z\"></sup>very great rejoicing.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And day by day, from the first day to the last day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12512AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12512AA\"></sup>he read from the Book of the Law of God. They kept the feast seven days, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12512AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12512AB\"></sup>on the eighth day there was a solemn assembly, according to the rule."
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>Now on the twenty-fourth day of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12513A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12513A\"></sup>this month the people of Israel were assembled <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12513B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12513B\"></sup>with fasting <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12513C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12513C\"></sup>and in sackcloth, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12513D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12513D\"></sup>and with earth on their heads.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12514E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12514E\"></sup>And the Israelites separated themselves from all foreigners and stood and confessed their sins and the iniquities of their fathers.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12515F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12515F\"></sup>And they stood up in their place and read from the Book of the Law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God for a quarter of the day; for another quarter of it they made confession and worshiped the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>On the stairs of the Levites stood <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12516G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12516G\"></sup>Jeshua, Bani, Kadmiel, Shebaniah, Bunni, Sherebiah, Bani, and Chenani; and they cried with a loud voice to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> their God.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the Levites, Jeshua, Kadmiel, Bani, Hashabneiah, Sherebiah, Hodiah, Shebaniah, and Pethahiah, said, “Stand up and bless the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> your God from everlasting to everlasting. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12517H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12517H\"></sup>Blessed be your glorious name, which is exalted above all blessing and praise.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12518I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12518I\"></sup>“You are the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, you alone. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12518J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12518J\"></sup>You have made heaven, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12518K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12518K\"></sup>the heaven of heavens, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12518L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12518L\"></sup>with all their host, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12518M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12518M\"></sup>the earth and all that is on it, the seas and all that is in them; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12518N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12518N\"></sup>and you preserve all of them; and the host of heaven worships you.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>You are the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12519O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12519O\"></sup>who chose Abram and brought him out of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12519P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12519P\"></sup>Ur of the Chaldeans <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12519Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12519Q\"></sup>and gave him the name Abraham.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12520R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12520R\"></sup>You found his heart faithful before you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12520S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12520S\"></sup>and made with him the covenant to give to his offspring <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12520T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12520T\"></sup>the land of the Canaanite, the Hittite, the Amorite, the Perizzite, the Jebusite, and the Girgashite. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12520U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12520U\"></sup>And you have kept your promise, for you are righteous.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12521V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12521V\"></sup>“And you saw the affliction of our fathers in Egypt and heard <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12521W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12521W\"></sup>their cry at the Red Sea,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12522X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12522X\"></sup>and performed signs and wonders against Pharaoh and all his servants and all the people of his land, for you knew that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12522Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12522Y\"></sup>they acted arrogantly against our fathers. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12522Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12522Z\"></sup>you made a name for yourself, as it is to this day.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12523AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12523AA\"></sup>And you divided the sea before them, so that they went through the midst of the sea on dry land, and you cast their pursuers into the depths, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12523AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12523AB\"></sup>as a stone into mighty waters.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>By <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12524AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12524AC\"></sup>a pillar of cloud you led them in the day, and by a pillar of fire in the night to light for them the way in which they should go.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12525AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12525AD\"></sup>You came down on Mount Sinai <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12525AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12525AE\"></sup>and spoke with them from heaven and gave them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12525AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12525AF\"></sup>right rules and true laws, good statutes and commandments,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12526AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12526AG\"></sup>and you made known to them your holy Sabbath and commanded them commandments and statutes and a law by Moses your servant.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12527AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12527AH\"></sup>You gave them bread from heaven for their hunger and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12527AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12527AI\"></sup>brought water for them out of the rock for their thirst, and you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12527AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12527AJ\"></sup>told them to go in to possess the land that you had sworn to give them.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“But they and our fathers <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12528AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12528AK\"></sup>acted presumptuously and stiffened their neck and did not obey your commandments.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>They refused to obey <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12529AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12529AL\"></sup>and were not mindful of the wonders that you performed among them, but they stiffened their neck and appointed a leader to return to their slavery in Egypt. But you are a God ready to forgive, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12529AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12529AM\"></sup>gracious and merciful, slow to anger and abounding in steadfast love, and did not forsake them.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Even <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12530AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12530AN\"></sup>when they had made for themselves a golden calf and said, ‘This is your God who brought you up out of Egypt,’ <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12530AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12530AO\"></sup>and had committed great blasphemies,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12531AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12531AP\"></sup>in your great mercies did not forsake them in the wilderness. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12531AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12531AQ\"></sup>The pillar of cloud to lead them in the way did not depart from them by day, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12531AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12531AR\"></sup>nor the pillar of fire by night to light for them the way by which they should go.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12532AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12532AS\"></sup>You gave your good Spirit to instruct them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12532AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12532AT\"></sup>and did not withhold your manna from their mouth and gave them water for their thirst.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12533AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12533AU\"></sup>Forty years you sustained them in the wilderness, and they lacked nothing. Their clothes did not wear out and their feet did not swell.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>“And you gave them kingdoms and peoples and allotted to them every corner. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12534AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12534AV\"></sup>So they took possession of the land of Sihon king of Heshbon <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12534AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12534AW\"></sup>and the land of Og king of Bashan.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>You multiplied their children <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12535AX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AX&quot;&gt;AX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12535AX\"></sup>as the stars of heaven, and you brought them into the land that you had told their fathers to enter and possess.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12536AY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AY&quot;&gt;AY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12536AY\"></sup>So the descendants went in and possessed the land, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12536AZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AZ&quot;&gt;AZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12536AZ\"></sup>and you subdued before them the inhabitants of the land, the Canaanites, and gave them into their hand, with their kings and the peoples of the land, that they might do with them as they would.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And they captured <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12537BA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BA&quot;&gt;BA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12537BA\"></sup>fortified cities and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12537BB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BB&quot;&gt;BB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12537BB\"></sup>a rich land, and took possession of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12537BC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BC&quot;&gt;BC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12537BC\"></sup>houses full of all good things, cisterns already hewn, vineyards, olive orchards and fruit trees in abundance. So they ate and were filled <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12537BD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BD&quot;&gt;BD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12537BD\"></sup>and became fat and delighted themselves in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12537BE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BE&quot;&gt;BE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12537BE\"></sup>your great goodness.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12538BF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BF&quot;&gt;BF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12538BF\"></sup>“Nevertheless, they were disobedient and rebelled against you <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12538BG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BG&quot;&gt;BG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12538BG\"></sup>and cast your law behind their back <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12538BH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BH&quot;&gt;BH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12538BH\"></sup>and killed your prophets, who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12538BI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BI&quot;&gt;BI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12538BI\"></sup>had warned them in order to turn them back to you, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12538BJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BJ&quot;&gt;BJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12538BJ\"></sup>and they committed great blasphemies.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12539BK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BK&quot;&gt;BK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12539BK\"></sup>Therefore you gave them into the hand of their enemies, who made them suffer. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12539BL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BL&quot;&gt;BL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12539BL\"></sup>And in the time of their suffering they cried out to you and you heard them from heaven, and according to your great mercies you gave them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12539BM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BM&quot;&gt;BM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12539BM\"></sup>saviors who saved them from the hand of their enemies.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12540BN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BN&quot;&gt;BN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12540BN\"></sup>But after they had rest they did evil again before you, and you abandoned them to the hand of their enemies, so that they had dominion over them. Yet when they turned and cried to you, you heard from heaven, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12540BO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BO&quot;&gt;BO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12540BO\"></sup>and many times you delivered them according to your mercies.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12541BP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BP&quot;&gt;BP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12541BP\"></sup>And you warned them in order to turn them back to your law. Yet <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12541BQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BQ&quot;&gt;BQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12541BQ\"></sup>they acted presumptuously and did not obey your commandments, but sinned against your rules, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12541BR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BR&quot;&gt;BR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12541BR\"></sup>which if a person does them, he shall live by them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12541BS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BS&quot;&gt;BS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12541BS\"></sup>and they turned a stubborn shoulder <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12541BT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BT&quot;&gt;BT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12541BT\"></sup>and stiffened their neck and would not obey.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Many years <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12542BU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BU&quot;&gt;BU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12542BU\"></sup>you bore with them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12542BV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BV&quot;&gt;BV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12542BV\"></sup>and warned them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12542BW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BW&quot;&gt;BW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12542BW\"></sup>by your Spirit through your prophets. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12542BX&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BX&quot;&gt;BX&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12542BX\"></sup>Yet they would not give ear. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12542BY&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BY&quot;&gt;BY&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12542BY\"></sup>Therefore you gave them into the hand of the peoples of the lands.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Nevertheless, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12543BZ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference BZ&quot;&gt;BZ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12543BZ\"></sup>in your great mercies <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12543CA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CA&quot;&gt;CA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12543CA\"></sup>you did not make an end of them or forsake them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12543CB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CB&quot;&gt;CB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12543CB\"></sup>for you are a gracious and merciful God.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“Now, therefore, our God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12544CC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CC&quot;&gt;CC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12544CC\"></sup>the great, the mighty, and the awesome God, who keeps covenant and steadfast love, let not all the hardship seem little to you that has come upon us, upon our kings, our princes, our priests, our prophets, our fathers, and all your people, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12544CD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CD&quot;&gt;CD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12544CD\"></sup>since the time of the kings of Assyria until this day.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12545CE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CE&quot;&gt;CE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12545CE\"></sup>Yet you have been righteous in all that has come upon us, for you have dealt faithfully <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12545CF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CF&quot;&gt;CF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12545CF\"></sup>and we have acted wickedly.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Our kings, our princes, our priests, and our fathers have not kept your law or paid attention to your commandments and your warnings that you gave them.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Even in their own kingdom, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12547CG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CG&quot;&gt;CG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12547CG\"></sup>and amid your great goodness that you gave them, and in the large and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12547CH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CH&quot;&gt;CH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12547CH\"></sup>rich land that you set before them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12547CI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CI&quot;&gt;CI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12547CI\"></sup>they did not serve you or turn from their wicked works.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Behold, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12548CJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CJ&quot;&gt;CJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12548CJ\"></sup>we are slaves this day; in the land that you gave to our fathers to enjoy its fruit and its good gifts, behold, we are slaves.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12549CK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CK&quot;&gt;CK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12549CK\"></sup>And its rich yield goes to the kings whom you have set over us because of our sins. They rule over our bodies and over our livestock as they please, and we are in great distress.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup> “Because of all this <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12550CL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CL&quot;&gt;CL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12550CL\"></sup>we make a firm covenant in writing; on <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12550CM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference CM&quot;&gt;CM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12550CM\"></sup>the sealed document are the names of our princes, our Levites, and our priests."
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span> <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12551A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12551A\"></sup>“On the seals are the names of Nehemiah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12551B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12551B\"></sup>the governor, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12551C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12551C\"></sup>the son of Hacaliah, Zedekiah,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12552D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12552D\"></sup>Seraiah, Azariah, Jeremiah,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Pashhur, Amariah, Malchijah,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12554E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12554E\"></sup>Hattush, Shebaniah, Malluch,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Harim, Meremoth, Obadiah,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Daniel, Ginnethon, Baruch,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Meshullam, Abijah, Mijamin,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Maaziah, Bilgai, Shemaiah; these are the priests.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And the Levites: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12559F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12559F\"></sup>Jeshua the son of Azaniah, Binnui of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12559G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12559G\"></sup>Henadad, Kadmiel;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and their brothers, Shebaniah, Hodiah, Kelita, Pelaiah, Hanan,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Mica, Rehob, Hashabiah,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Zaccur, Sherebiah, Shebaniah,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Hodiah, Bani, Beninu.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>The chiefs of the people: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12564H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12564H\"></sup>Parosh, Pahath-moab, Elam, Zattu, Bani,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Bunni, Azgad, Bebai,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Adonijah, Bigvai, Adin,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Ater, Hezekiah, Azzur,",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Hodiah, Hashum, Bezai,",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Hariph, Anathoth, Nebai,",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Magpiash, Meshullam, Hezir,",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Meshezabel, Zadok, Jaddua,",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Pelatiah, Hanan, Anaiah,",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Hoshea, Hananiah, Hasshub,",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Hallohesh, Pilha, Shobek,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Rehum, Hashabnah, Maaseiah,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Ahiah, Hanan, Anan,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Malluch, Harim, Baanah.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12578I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12578I\"></sup>“The rest of the people, the priests, the Levites, the gatekeepers, the singers, the temple servants, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12578J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12578J\"></sup>and all who have separated themselves from the peoples of the lands to the Law of God, their wives, their sons, their daughters, all who have knowledge and understanding,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>join with their brothers, their nobles, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12579K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12579K\"></sup>and enter into a curse and an oath <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12579L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12579L\"></sup>to walk in God's Law that was given by Moses the servant of God, and to observe and do all the commandments of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our Lord and his rules and his statutes.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12580M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12580M\"></sup>We will not give our daughters to the peoples of the land or take their daughters for our sons.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12581N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12581N\"></sup>And if the peoples of the land bring in goods or any grain on the Sabbath day to sell, we will not buy from them on the Sabbath or on a holy day. And we will forego the crops of the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12581O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12581O\"></sup>seventh year and the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12581P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12581P\"></sup>exaction of every debt.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>“We also take on ourselves the obligation to give yearly <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12582Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12582Q\"></sup>a third part of a shekel for the service of the house of our God:",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12583R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12583R\"></sup>for the showbread, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12583S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12583S\"></sup>the regular grain offering, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12583T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12583T\"></sup>the regular burnt offering, the Sabbaths, the new moons, the appointed feasts, the holy things, and the sin offerings to make atonement for Israel, and for all the work of the house of our God.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12584U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12584U\"></sup>We, the priests, the Levites, and the people, have likewise cast lots <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12584V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12584V\"></sup>for the wood offering, to bring it into the house of our God, according to our fathers' houses, at times appointed, year by year, to burn on the altar of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12584W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12584W\"></sup>as it is written in the Law.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>We obligate ourselves <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12585X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12585X\"></sup>to bring the firstfruits of our ground and the firstfruits of all fruit of every tree, year by year, to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>;",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>also to bring to the house of our God, to the priests who minister in the house of our God, the firstborn of our sons and of our cattle, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12586Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12586Y\"></sup>as it is written in the Law, and the firstborn of our herds and of our flocks;",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12587Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12587Z\"></sup>and to bring the first of our dough, and our contributions, the fruit of every tree, the wine and the oil, to the priests, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12587AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12587AA\"></sup>to the chambers of the house of our God; and to bring to the Levites the tithes from our ground, for it is the Levites who collect the tithes in all our towns where we labor.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>And the priest, the son of Aaron, shall be with the Levites when the Levites receive the tithes. And the Levites shall bring up the tithe of the tithes to the house of our God, to the chambers of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12588AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12588AB\"></sup>the storehouse.",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>For the people of Israel and the sons of Levi <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12589AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12589AC\"></sup>shall bring the contribution of grain, wine, and oil to the chambers, where the vessels of the sanctuary are, as well as the priests who minister, and the gatekeepers and the singers. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12589AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12589AD\"></sup>We will not neglect the house of our God.”"
		},
		"11": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">11 </span>Now the leaders of the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12590A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12590A\"></sup>lived in Jerusalem. And the rest of the people <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12590B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12590B\"></sup>cast lots to bring one out of ten to live in Jerusalem <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12590C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12590C\"></sup>the holy city, while nine out of ten remained in the other towns.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>And the people blessed all the men <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12591D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12591D\"></sup>who willingly offered to live in Jerusalem.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12592E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12592E\"></sup>These are the chiefs of the province who lived in Jerusalem; but in the towns of Judah <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12592F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12592F\"></sup>everyone lived on his property in their towns: Israel, the priests, the Levites, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12592G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12592G\"></sup>the temple servants, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12592H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12592H\"></sup>and the descendants of Solomon's servants.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And in Jerusalem lived certain of the sons of Judah and of the sons of Benjamin. Of the sons of Judah: Athaiah the son of Uzziah, son of Zechariah, son of Amariah, son of Shephatiah, son of Mahalalel, of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12593I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12593I\"></sup>Perez;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>and Maaseiah the son of Baruch, son of Col-hozeh, son of Hazaiah, son of Adaiah, son of Joiarib, son of Zechariah, son of the Shilonite.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>All the sons of Perez who lived in Jerusalem were 468 valiant men.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And these are the sons of Benjamin: Sallu the son of Meshullam, son of Joed, son of Pedaiah, son of Kolaiah, son of Maaseiah, son of Ithiel, son of Jeshaiah,",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>and his brothers, men of valor, 928.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Joel the son of Zichri was their overseer; and Judah the son of Hassenuah was second over the city.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Of the priests: Jedaiah the son of Joiarib, Jachin,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Seraiah the son of Hilkiah, son of Meshullam, son of Zadok, son of Meraioth, son of Ahitub, ruler of the house of God,",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>and their brothers who did the work of the house, 822; and Adaiah the son of Jeroham, son of Pelaliah, son of Amzi, son of Zechariah, son of Pashhur, son of Malchijah,",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>and his brothers, heads of fathers' houses, 242; and Amashsai, the son of Azarel, son of Ahzai, son of Meshillemoth, son of Immer,",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>and their brothers, mighty men of valor, 128; their overseer was Zabdiel the son of Haggedolim.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>And of the Levites: Shemaiah the son of Hasshub, son of Azrikam, son of Hashabiah, son of Bunni;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>and Shabbethai and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12605J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12605J\"></sup>Jozabad, of the chiefs of the Levites, who were over <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12605K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12605K\"></sup>the outside work of the house of God;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12606L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12606L\"></sup>Mattaniah the son of Mica, son of Zabdi, son of Asaph, who was the leader of the praise, who gave thanks, and Bakbukiah, the second among his brothers; and Abda the son of Shammua, son of Galal, son of Jeduthun.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>All the Levites in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12607M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12607M\"></sup>the holy city were 284.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>The gatekeepers, Akkub, Talmon and their brothers, who kept watch at the gates, were 172.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And the rest of Israel, and of the priests and the Levites, were in all the towns of Judah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12609N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12609N\"></sup>every one in his inheritance.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12610O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12610O\"></sup>But the temple servants lived on Ophel; and Ziha and Gishpa were over the temple servants.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>The overseer of the Levites in Jerusalem was Uzzi the son of Bani, son of Hashabiah, son of Mattaniah, son of Mica, of the sons of Asaph, the singers, over the work of the house of God.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12612P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12612P\"></sup>For there was a command from the king concerning them, and a fixed provision for the singers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12612Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12612Q\"></sup>as every day required.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And Pethahiah the son of Meshezabel, of the sons of Zerah the son of Judah, was at the king's side in all matters concerning the people.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And as for the villages, with their fields, some of the people of Judah lived in <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12614R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12614R\"></sup>Kiriath-arba and its villages, and in Dibon and its villages, and in Jekabzeel and its villages,",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>and in Jeshua and in Moladah and Beth-pelet,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>in Hazar-shual, in Beersheba and its villages,",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>in Ziklag, in Meconah and its villages,",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>in En-rimmon, in Zorah, in Jarmuth,",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Zanoah, Adullam, and their villages, Lachish and its fields, and Azekah and its villages. So they encamped from Beersheba to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12619S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12619S\"></sup>the Valley of Hinnom.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>The people of Benjamin also lived from Geba onward, at Michmash, Aija, Bethel and its villages,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Anathoth, Nob, Ananiah,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>Hazor, Ramah, Gittaim,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Hadid, Zeboim, Neballat,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Lod, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12624T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12624T\"></sup>Ono, the valley of craftsmen.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>And certain divisions of the Levites in Judah were assigned to Benjamin."
		},
		"12": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">12 </span>These are <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12626A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12626A\"></sup>the priests and the Levites who came up with <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12626B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12626B\"></sup>Zerubbabel the son of Shealtiel, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12626C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12626C\"></sup>Jeshua: <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12626D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12626D\"></sup>Seraiah, Jeremiah, Ezra,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Amariah, Malluch, Hattush,",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Shecaniah, Rehum, Meremoth,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Iddo, Ginnethoi, Abijah,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Mijamin, Maadiah, Bilgah,",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Shemaiah, Joiarib, Jedaiah,",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Sallu, Amok, Hilkiah, Jedaiah. These were the chiefs of the priests and of their brothers in the days of Jeshua.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And the Levites: Jeshua, Binnui, Kadmiel, Sherebiah, Judah, and Mattaniah, who with his brothers was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12633E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12633E\"></sup>in charge of the songs of thanksgiving.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>And Bakbukiah and Unni and their brothers stood opposite them <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12634F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12634F\"></sup>in the service.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>And Jeshua was the father of Joiakim, Joiakim the father of Eliashib, Eliashib the father of Joiada,",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Joiada the father of Jonathan, and Jonathan the father of Jaddua.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12637G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12637G\"></sup>And in the days of Joiakim were priests, heads of fathers' houses: of Seraiah, Meraiah; of Jeremiah, Hananiah;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>of Ezra, Meshullam; of Amariah, Jehohanan;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>of Malluchi, Jonathan; of Shebaniah, Joseph;",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>of Harim, Adna; of Meraioth, Helkai;",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>of Iddo, Zechariah; of Ginnethon, Meshullam;",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>of Abijah, Zichri; of Miniamin, of Moadiah, Piltai;",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>of Bilgah, Shammua; of Shemaiah, Jehonathan;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>of Joiarib, Mattenai; of Jedaiah, Uzzi;",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>of Sallai, Kallai; of Amok, Eber;",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>of Hilkiah, Hashabiah; of Jedaiah, Nethanel.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>In the days of Eliashib, Joiada, Johanan, and Jaddua, the Levites were recorded as heads of fathers' houses; so too were the priests in the reign of Darius the Persian.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>As for the sons of Levi, their heads of fathers' houses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12648H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12648H\"></sup>were written in the Book of the Chronicles until the days of Johanan the son of Eliashib.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And the chiefs of the Levites: Hashabiah, Sherebiah, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12649I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12649I\"></sup>Jeshua the son of Kadmiel, with their brothers who stood opposite them, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12649J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12649J\"></sup>to praise and to give thanks, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12649K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12649K\"></sup>according to the commandment of David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12649L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12649L\"></sup>the man of God, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12649M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12649M\"></sup>watch by watch.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>Mattaniah, Bakbukiah, Obadiah, Meshullam, Talmon, and Akkub were gatekeepers standing guard at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12650N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12650N\"></sup>the storehouses of the gates.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>These were in the days of Joiakim the son of Jeshua son of Jozadak, and in the days of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12651O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12651O\"></sup>Nehemiah the governor and of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12651P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12651P\"></sup>Ezra, the priest and scribe.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>And at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12652Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12652Q\"></sup>the dedication of the wall of Jerusalem they sought the Levites in all their places, to bring them to Jerusalem to celebrate the dedication with gladness, with thanksgivings and with singing, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12652R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12652R\"></sup>with cymbals, harps, and lyres.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And the sons of the singers gathered together from the district surrounding Jerusalem and from the villages of the Netophathites;",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>also from Beth-gilgal and from the region of Geba and Azmaveth, for the singers had built for themselves villages around Jerusalem.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>And the priests and the Levites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12655S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12655S\"></sup>purified themselves, and they purified the people and the gates and the wall.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>Then I brought the leaders of Judah up onto the wall and appointed two great choirs that gave thanks. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12656T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12656T\"></sup>One went to the south on the wall to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12656U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12656U\"></sup>the Dung Gate.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>And after them went Hoshaiah and half of the leaders of Judah,",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>and Azariah, Ezra, Meshullam,",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Judah, Benjamin, Shemaiah, and Jeremiah,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>and certain of the priests' sons <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12660V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12660V\"></sup>with trumpets: Zechariah the son of Jonathan, son of Shemaiah, son of Mattaniah, son of Micaiah, son of Zaccur, son of Asaph;",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>and his relatives, Shemaiah, Azarel, Milalai, Gilalai, Maai, Nethanel, Judah, and Hanani, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12661W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12661W\"></sup>with the musical instruments of David <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12661X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12661X\"></sup>the man of God. And Ezra the scribe went before them.",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>At <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12662Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12662Y\"></sup>the Fountain Gate they went up straight before them by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12662Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12662Z\"></sup>the stairs of the city of David, at the ascent of the wall, above the house of David, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12662AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12662AA\"></sup>the Water Gate on the east.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12663AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12663AB\"></sup>The other choir of those who gave thanks went to the north, and I followed them with half of the people, on the wall, above <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12663AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12663AC\"></sup>the Tower of the Ovens, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12663AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12663AD\"></sup>the Broad Wall,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>and above <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12664AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12664AE\"></sup>the Gate of Ephraim, and by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12664AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12664AF\"></sup>the Gate of Yeshanah, and by <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12664AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12664AG\"></sup>the Fish Gate and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12664AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12664AH\"></sup>the Tower of Hananel and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12664AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12664AI\"></sup>the Tower of the Hundred, to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12664AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12664AJ\"></sup>the Sheep Gate; and they came to a halt at <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12664AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12664AK\"></sup>the Gate of the Guard.",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>So both choirs of those who gave thanks stood in the house of God, and I and half of the officials with me;",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>and the priests Eliakim, Maaseiah, Miniamin, Micaiah, Elioenai, Zechariah, and Hananiah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12666AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12666AL\"></sup>with trumpets;",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>and Maaseiah, Shemaiah, Eleazar, Uzzi, Jehohanan, Malchijah, Elam, and Ezer. And the singers sang with Jezrahiah as their leader.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>And they offered great sacrifices that day and rejoiced, for God had made them rejoice with great joy; the women and children also rejoiced. And the joy of Jerusalem was heard far away.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12669AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12669AM\"></sup>On that day men were appointed over the storerooms, the contributions, the firstfruits, and the tithes, to gather into them the portions required by the Law for the priests and for the Levites according to the fields of the towns, for Judah rejoiced over the priests and the Levites who ministered.",
			"45": "<sup class=\"versenum\">45 </sup>And they performed the service of their God and the service of purification, as did the singers and the gatekeepers, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12670AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12670AN\"></sup>according to the command of David and his son Solomon.",
			"46": "<sup class=\"versenum\">46 </sup>For long ago in the days of David and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12671AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12671AO\"></sup>Asaph there were directors of the singers, and there were songs of praise and thanksgiving to God.",
			"47": "<sup class=\"versenum\">47 </sup>And all Israel in the days of Zerubbabel and in the days of Nehemiah gave the <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12672AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12672AP\"></sup>daily portions for the singers and the gatekeepers; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12672AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12672AQ\"></sup>and they set apart that which was for the Levites; <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12672AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12672AR\"></sup>and the Levites set apart that which was for the sons of Aaron."
		},
		"13": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">13 </span>On that day <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12673A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12673A\"></sup>they read from the Book of Moses in the hearing of the people. And in it was found written <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12673B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12673B\"></sup>that no Ammonite or Moabite should ever enter the assembly of God,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>for they did not meet the people of Israel with bread and water, but hired Balaam against them to curse them—yet our God turned the curse into a blessing.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>As soon as the people heard the law, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12675C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12675C\"></sup>they separated from Israel all <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12675D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12675D\"></sup>those of foreign descent.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Now before this, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12676E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12676E\"></sup>Eliashib the priest, who <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12676F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12676F\"></sup>was appointed over the chambers of the house of our God, and who was related to <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12676G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12676G\"></sup>Tobiah,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>prepared for Tobiah a large chamber where they had previously put the grain offering, the frankincense, the vessels, and the tithes of grain, wine, and oil, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12677H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12677H\"></sup>which were given by commandment to the Levites, singers, and gatekeepers, and the contributions for the priests.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>While this was taking place, I was not in Jerusalem, for <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12678I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12678I\"></sup>in the thirty-second year of Artaxerxes <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12678J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12678J\"></sup>king of Babylon I went to the king. And after some time I asked leave of the king",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>and came to Jerusalem, and I then discovered the evil that Eliashib had done for Tobiah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12679K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12679K\"></sup>preparing for him a chamber in the courts of the house of God.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>And I was very angry, and I threw all the household furniture of Tobiah out of the chamber.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Then I gave orders, and they <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12681L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12681L\"></sup>cleansed the chambers, and I brought back there the vessels of the house of God, with the grain offering and the frankincense.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>I also found out that <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12682M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12682M\"></sup>the portions of the Levites had not been given to them, so that the Levites and the singers, who did the work, had fled each <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12682N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12682N\"></sup>to his field.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12683O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12683O\"></sup>So I confronted the officials and said, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12683P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12683P\"></sup>“Why is the house of God forsaken?” And I gathered them together and set them in their stations.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Then all Judah brought <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12684Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12684Q\"></sup>the tithe of the grain, wine, and oil into the storehouses.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12685R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12685R\"></sup>I appointed as treasurers over the storehouses Shelemiah the priest, Zadok the scribe, and Pedaiah of the Levites, and as their assistant Hanan the son of Zaccur, son of Mattaniah, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12685S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12685S\"></sup>for they were considered reliable, and their duty was to distribute to their brothers.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12686T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12686T\"></sup>Remember me, O my God, concerning this, and do not wipe out my good deeds that I have done for the house of my God and for his service.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>In those days I saw in Judah people treading winepresses <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12687U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12687U\"></sup>on the Sabbath, and bringing in heaps of grain and loading them on donkeys, and also wine, grapes, figs, and all kinds of loads, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12687V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12687V\"></sup>which they brought into Jerusalem on the Sabbath day. And <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12687W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12687W\"></sup>I warned them on the day when they sold food.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Tyrians also, who lived in the city, brought in fish and all kinds of goods and sold them on the Sabbath to the people of Judah, in Jerusalem itself!",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12689X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12689X\"></sup>Then I confronted the nobles of Judah and said to them, “What is this evil thing that you are doing, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12689Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12689Y\"></sup>profaning the Sabbath day?",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12690Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12690Z\"></sup>Did not your fathers act in this way, and did not our God bring all this disaster on us and on this city? Now you are bringing more wrath on Israel by profaning the Sabbath.”",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>As soon as it <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12691AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12691AA\"></sup>began to grow dark at the gates of Jerusalem before the Sabbath, I commanded that the doors should be shut and gave orders that they should not be opened until after the Sabbath. And I stationed some of my servants at the gates, that no load might be brought in on the Sabbath day.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Then the merchants and sellers of all kinds of wares lodged outside Jerusalem once or twice.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12693AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12693AB\"></sup>But I warned them and said to them, “Why do you lodge outside the wall? If you do so again, I will lay hands on you.” From that time on they did not come on the Sabbath.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Then I commanded the Levites <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12694AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12694AC\"></sup>that they should purify themselves and come and guard the gates, to keep the Sabbath day holy. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12694AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12694AD\"></sup>Remember this also in my favor, O my God, and spare me according to the greatness of your steadfast love.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>In those days also I saw the Jews <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12695AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12695AE\"></sup>who had married women <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12695AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12695AF\"></sup>of Ashdod, <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12695AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12695AG\"></sup>Ammon, and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12695AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12695AH\"></sup>Moab.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>And half of their children spoke the language of Ashdod, and they could not speak the language of Judah, but only the language of each people.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12697AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12697AI\"></sup>And I confronted them and cursed them and beat some of them and pulled out their hair. <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12697AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12697AJ\"></sup>And I made them take an oath in the name of God, saying, “You shall not give your daughters to their sons, or take their daughters for your sons or for yourselves.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12698AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12698AK\"></sup>Did not Solomon king of Israel sin on account of such women? <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12698AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12698AL\"></sup>Among the many nations there was no king like him, and he was <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12698AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12698AM\"></sup>beloved by his God, and God made him king over all Israel. Nevertheless, foreign women made even him to sin.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Shall we then listen to you and do all this great evil and <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12699AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12699AN\"></sup>act treacherously against our God by marrying foreign women?”",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>And one of the sons of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12700AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12700AO\"></sup>Jehoiada, the son of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12700AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12700AP\"></sup>Eliashib the high priest, was the son-in-law of <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12700AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12700AQ\"></sup>Sanballat the Horonite. Therefore I chased him from me.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12701AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12701AR\"></sup>Remember them, O my God, because they have desecrated the priesthood <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12701AS&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AS&quot;&gt;AS&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12701AS\"></sup>and the covenant of the priesthood and the Levites.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup><sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12702AT&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AT&quot;&gt;AT&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12702AT\"></sup>Thus I cleansed them from everything foreign, and I established the duties of the priests and Levites, each in his work;",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>and I provided <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12703AU&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AU&quot;&gt;AU&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12703AU\"></sup>for the wood offering <sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12703AV&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AV&quot;&gt;AV&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12703AV\"></sup>at appointed times, and for the firstfruits.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-ESV-12703AW&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AW&quot;&gt;AW&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-ESV-12703AW\"></sup>Remember me, O my God, for good."
		}
	}
};
module.exports = book;